2. Create a polarization map with several map output files of 'fintab'
task. The plot will include just the polarization vectors with the
star position in the middle of the associated vector. The map
reference image is overplotted in negative mode. The polarization
scale is also included. The parameters set and the file list are
showed.

.nf
pc> lpar vecplot
   (files_txt = "@map")         input file with vectors (.txt)
    (file_img = "map.fits")     reference image (.imh,.fits)
     (file_ps = "test")         output postscript file
         (bin = 1.)             scale for binning (pixels)
       (devps = "psi_port")     postscript device to use
       (xorig = 1.)             x-origin for image offset
       (yorig = 1.)             y-origin for image offset
        (pvec = yes)            plot vectors?
      (posvec = "middle")       vector position respect to object?
      (escala = 1000.)          scale plot
      (titulo = "map")          title string?
 (escalatitle = yes)            title with scale?
      (pimage = yes)            overplot image?
  (niveisfull = no)             lower and higher zrange levels?
          (z1 = 1211.)          custom lower zrange level?
          (z2 = 3345.)          custom higher zrange level?
      (mapsao = "none")         saocmap file name
     (typeimg = yes)            negative image?
    (typestar = no)             plot star number?
 (reposiciona = no)             locus of star number repositioned?
    (typefont = "small")        character size
        (pext = no)             plot the extinction?
    (file_ext = "")             extinction image
     (newcont = "")             newcont parameters (:e to edit)
      (flist0 = "")
      (flist1 = "")
       (line1 = "")
        (mode = "ql")

